## STEP 7 — PRODUCT REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (PRD)

**This is the primary business deliverable.** Synthesize everything from Steps 1–6.

```markdown
# Product Requirements Document
## [Application Name] — Reverse Engineered from Codebase
**Version**: 1.0 (Auto-generated)  
**Source**: [repo name / path]  
**Generated**: [date]  
**Stack**: [Java X + JSF X / Spring Boot X]

---

## 1. Executive Summary

### 1.1 Product Overview
[2–3 paragraphs describing what the application does, who uses it, and what
business problem it solves. Infer from: domain entity names, screen names,
controller paths, package names, exception messages, and validation rules.]

### 1.2 Business Context
[Who is the primary user? What department or business process does this support?
Infer from: entity names (Order, Invoice, Patient, Employee), screen names, roles.]

### 1.3 Key Metrics / Scale Signals
[Infer from: pagination settings, caching config, batch job sizes, DB indexes,
connection pool settings. E.g. "Pagination at 25 rows suggests medium data volumes."]

---

## 2. User Roles & Permissions

[Infer from Spring Security config, @Secured, @PreAuthorize, role enums, session beans]

| Role | Description | Key Permissions |
|------|-------------|-----------------|
| [ROLE_ADMIN] | [inferred description] | [what they can do] |
| [ROLE_USER] | [inferred description] | [what they can do] |
| [ROLE_MANAGER] | [inferred description] | [what they can do] |

---

## 3. Functional Requirements

### 3.1 Feature Areas
[Group by domain module, screen group, or controller group]

#### Feature Area 1: [e.g. Order Management]
| ID | Requirement | Source (code location) | Priority (infer) |
|----|-------------|----------------------|------------------|
| FR-001 | User can create a new order with line items | OrderCreateBean.save() | HIGH |
| FR-002 | User can search orders by date range and status | OrderListBean.search() | HIGH |
| FR-003 | System validates order total > 0 before saving | OrderService validation | HIGH |
| FR-004 | Admin can export order list to CSV | OrderListBean.export() | MED |

#### Feature Area 2: [next domain area]
...

### 3.2 Screen-by-Screen Requirements
[For each screen in the Screen Inventory, derive requirements]

#### [Screen Name] (screen.xhtml)
- **Purpose**: [what the user accomplishes on this screen]
- **User Stories**:
  - As a [role], I can [action] so that [outcome]
  - ...
- **Business Rules Applied**: [list BR-XXX codes]
- **Data Displayed**: [entity fields shown]
- **Actions Available**: [buttons / operations]

---

## 4. Non-Functional Requirements

### 4.1 Performance
[Infer from: connection pool size, caching annotations, pagination config,
@Async usage, lazy loading settings]
- [ ] Page load: [infer from architecture — JSF postback model vs REST]
- [ ] Concurrent users: [infer from thread pool / session config]

### 4.2 Security
[Infer from Spring Security config, HTTPS config, CSRF settings, session config]
- Authentication: [form login / OAuth2 / SAML / LDAP / custom]
- Authorization: [role-based / method-level / URL-level]
- Session management: [timeout value if found]
- CSRF protection: [enabled/disabled]
- Password policy: [if found in code]

### 4.3 Data Integrity
[Infer from @Transactional, FK constraints in migrations, validation annotations]
- Transactions: [how they're managed]
- Validation: [where applied — client / service / entity]
- Referential integrity: [FK constraints found in SQL migrations]

### 4.4 Deployment & Environment
[Infer from Dockerfile, profiles, Makefile, README]
- Target environment: [embedded Tomcat / JBoss / WAR deployment]
- Configuration profiles: [dev, staging, prod — what each changes]
- External dependencies: [DB, message broker, external APIs]

---

## 5. Data Requirements

### 5.1 Core Entities
[Paste Entity Relationship Summary from Step 5]

### 5.2 Data Retention / Lifecycle
[Infer from: soft delete fields (isDeleted, active), audit fields (createdAt, updatedAt),
archive tables, scheduled cleanup jobs]

### 5.3 Reporting & Export
[Infer from: export methods, JasperReports/BIRT usage, scheduled report jobs,
PDF generation libraries]

---

## 6. Integration Requirements

```bash
# Detect external integrations
grep -rn "RestTemplate\|WebClient\|RestClient\|FeignClient\|HttpClient\|URLConnection" \
  --include="*.java" . | grep -v test | grep -v target | head -20

grep -rn "@WebServiceClient\|@WebService\|SOAPMessage\|JAXBContext" \
  --include="*.java" . | grep -v test | grep -v target | head -10

grep -rn "JmsTemplate\|KafkaTemplate\|RabbitTemplate\|SqsClient" \
  --include="*.java" . | grep -v test | grep -v target | head -10
```

| Integration | Type | Direction | Purpose |
|-------------|------|-----------|---------|
| [System name] | REST / SOAP / JMS / Kafka | Inbound / Outbound | [inferred purpose] |

---

## 7. Assumptions & Open Questions

[List things that could not be determined from code alone]

- ❓ **[Topic]**: [What was unclear and why]
- ❓ **Business owner**: Could not be determined from code
- ❓ **SLA / uptime requirement**: Not found in configuration
- ❓ **[Screen/feature]**: Logic present but business intent unclear

---

## 8. Recommended Improvements

[From Step 4 legacy flags — translate technical debt into business risk language]

| Issue | Business Risk | Recommendation |
|-------|--------------|----------------|
| Spring Boot 1.x (EOL) | Security vulnerabilities, no vendor patches | Upgrade to Spring Boot 3.x |
| No test coverage | High regression risk during changes | Add JUnit 5 + integration tests |
| WebSecurityConfigurerAdapter (deprecated) | Future incompatibility | Migrate to SecurityFilterChain |
| Field @Autowired throughout | Developer velocity drag | Refactor to constructor injection |
```

---

## STEP 8 — DEVELOPER QUICK-START

```markdown
# Developer Quick-Start

## Prerequistes
[Infer from pom.xml / build.gradle: JDK version, Maven/Gradle version]

## Run Locally
[Infer from README, Makefile, docker-compose.yml, application-local.properties]

## Key Configuration
[List the most important application.properties / application.yml keys]

## Package Structure
```
src/main/java/
  com.example.[domain]/
    controller/     ← Spring MVC @Controller or JSF backing beans  
    service/        ← Business logic (@Service)
    repository/     ← Data access (@Repository / JpaRepository)
    entity/         ← JPA @Entity classes
    dto/            ← Data Transfer Objects
    config/         ← @Configuration classes
    security/       ← Spring Security config
src/main/resources/
  application.yml   ← Main configuration
  db/migration/     ← Flyway SQL migrations
src/main/webapp/
  WEB-INF/
    faces-config.xml ← JSF navigation + beans (legacy)
  pages/            ← XHTML Facelets views
```

## Top 5 Classes to Read First
[List actual class names found — most important service + controller + entity]
```

