## QUALITY CHECKLIST

Before delivering:

- [ ] Every file path referenced actually exists in the repo
- [ ] No invented class names or package paths
- [ ] JSF version confirmed (1.x vs 2.x vs 3.x vs 4.x)
- [ ] Spring era confirmed (XML / Boot 1 / Boot 2 / Boot 3)
- [ ] Java version confirmed from build files
- [ ] PRD Section 1 written in plain business English (no Java jargon)
- [ ] Business Rules are phrased as rules, not code descriptions
- [ ] Screen Inventory covers every .xhtml file found
- [ ] Open Questions section is honest about gaps
- [ ] Recommended Improvements framed as business risk, not tech debt
